1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Attention, everyone! Jim and I, on behalf of the party planning committee, have it announced

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,000
— Too loud. Too loud. Too loud.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
— but effective. Look. On behalf of Jim and I, Merry Christmas.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Merry Christmas, Jim.

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Merry Christmas. Good. My diabolical plot is on hold for Christmas. My heart just melts

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
with the sound of children singing.

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Not really. I'm just tired. The days are short. I don't know. Maybe I'm depressed.

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,000
It is time to unveil the tree.

9
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Rockefeller Center.

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Yeah.

11
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
I've actually been to Rock Center and this is nothing like that.

12
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,000
This is all we have.

13
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Ugh.

14
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
No, it's not ugh. It is office camaraderie.

15
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,000
It is warm feelings.

16
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Why don't we talk more about it instead of doing it?

17
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Thirty. Twenty-nine. Twenty-eight.

18
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Why would you start so high?

19
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Twenty-seven.

20
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Three. Twenty-six.

21
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Twenty-six.

22
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,000
One.

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Jim.

24
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Oh. You didn't decorate it.

25
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
No.

26
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Exactly.

27
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
We didn't because we think it would be better to do it together.

28
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Everyone, why would you wrap it in a sheet if you're not covering anything up?

29
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Is it fake?

30
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Pam.

31
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Yes. We are unveiling an artificial tree that will never die.

32
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Yes.

33
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Like the spirit of Christmas.

34
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
We're supposed to applaud you for taking a giant diabolical fake tree.

35
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
This was a successful unveiling. Go back to work.

36
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Merry Christmas.

37
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Hello. Sorry, guys. Sorry, guys.

38
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,000
I'm not sure I've earned the right to make announcements yet,

39
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:57,000
but whoever is giving me the 12 days of Christmas as my Secret Santa, please stop.

40
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
I can't take it anymore.

41
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,000
My cat killed a turtle dove.

42
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:05,000
The French hens have started pulling out my hair to make a nest.

43
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Please stop.

44
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
What psycho would send that as a gift?

45
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
I begged Dwight and Jim to give me Erin for Secret Santa,

46
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
and I decided to give Erin the 12 days of Christmas.

47
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Both die, guys.

48
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Is it my fault that the first eight days is basically 30 birds?

49
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Ho, ho, ho. Merry Christmas, boys and girls. It's me, Santa Claus.

50
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Hey, Santa.

51
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
They finally let you do it.

52
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Congrats, Phil.

53
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
It's so edgy.

54
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,000
I've been wanting to be Santa for years.

55
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:42,000
I believe I have the right temperament and the figure to do the job well.

56
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:46,000
I slipped a note to Jim 11 weeks ago, and he said I could do it.

57
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:56,000
It's been a long journey, but I'm Santa Claus.

58
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
So, Santa, what can we expect from this party?

59
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,000
It's going to be a very jolly time if you've been good.

60
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
What if you've been bad?

61
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Oh, then nothing but a lump of coal for you.

62
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:11,000
What if you've been really, really bad, more evil and strictly wrong?

63
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Hey, Creed, we covered it. Lump of coal.

64
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Yeah.

65
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:20,000
For the past several weeks, my secret Santa has been giving me pieces of a machine that I've been attempting to assemble.

66
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:27,000
I'm suspicious of this because I had the exact same idea for catching Osama Bin Laden.

67
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,000
I would simply send him a different piece each day.

68
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,000
He would assemble it to find himself in jail.

69
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:41,000
You know, Oscar, every time I make this lasagna, people ask me if it's a family recipe.

70
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:45,000
But really, I just get the recipe from the box.

71
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
That's funny.

72
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Is it funny? I thought it was more interesting than funny.

73
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,000
I think my water just broke.

74
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,000
That's too funny.

75
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Oscar and the warehouse guy.

76
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Go, Oscar!

77
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Go, gay warehouse guy!

78
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
Here's Santa!

79
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Hey, little girl, what would you like for Christmas?

80
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Ooh, you have been a very naughty girl, I see.

81
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
Michael, we already have a Santa. Phyllis.

82
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
What the hell is going on?

83
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Phyllis, Jim, Phyllis and Santa.

84
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Yeah.

85
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Phyllis.

86
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Yeah, I told her a long time ago she could do it.

87
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Take it back. That is absurd.

88
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
No, I can't do that.

89
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
No, Jim, come on!

90
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,000
I think she's doing a good job.

91
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Lately there have been serious rumors that our company is going bankrupt.

92
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
So David Wallace asked me to keep morale high.

93
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
So I asked around about what people wanted with Christmas.

94
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,000
And I told them to get creative.

95
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:47,000
And they didn't really get creative exactly.

96
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Secret Santa, karaoke, food.

97
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Kind of the usual thing that we do here, which is great.

98
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:58,000
And people usually argue about food, so I told everybody to bring their favorites.

99
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:02,000
I made an organized sign-up sheet for karaoke so that there was no fighting.

100
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,000
And no crying.

101
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
I'm doing a good job, I think.

102
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Because this year I care.

103
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,000
It's weird.

104
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,000
I know.

105
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
It's insane! A woman Santa? Where does it stop?

106
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
No! Jim, this may be the last Christmas that we have here.

107
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Doesn't it make you a tiny bit anxious?

108
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Me not playing Santa? Come on!

109
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,000
I'm not going to go tell Phyllis that she can't be Santa.

110
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Fine. Then do it anonymously. Ransom note style.

111
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,000
You can... You know what?

112
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:39,000
I have a bunch of letters cut out of magazines in my desk. You can use those.

113
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,000
If this were Russia, yeah, sure.

114
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Everybody would go to one Santa.

115
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,000
And there would be a line around the block.

116
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,000
And once you sat on her lap and she asked you what you wanted, you would say probably,

117
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Freedom. At which point the KGB would arrest you and send you to Siberia.

118
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,000
It's a good thing Russia doesn't exist anymore.

119
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,000
Name?

120
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Kelly.

121
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,000
And what would you like for Christmas?

122
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:05,000
I would like the photographer, please, Santa.

123
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Good.

124
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:10,000
So far, people really seem to like the party this year.

125
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,000
We took some chances and it's working out.

126
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Ho, ho, ho! Ho, ho, ho!

127
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:24,000
Why pay more to sit next to old tranny claws over there when you can sit on my lap?

128
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,000
Phyllis is only pretending to be a man.

129
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,000
I'm the real thing.

130
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Sit down on my lap and there will be no doubt.

131
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Okay.

132
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,000
No, it's not. It's not, like, penis-wise.

133
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Hello, little boy. What's your name?

134
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Michael, it's me, Kevin.

135
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Phyllis says I'm too big for her lap.

136
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:48,000
Oh, I am so sorry that Phyllis hates you and hates your body.

137
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:54,000
But Santa remembers a reindeer that was just a tiny bit different as well.

138
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
When can I sit on your lap?

139
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
Right now! Come on over here, big boy!

140
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,000
There we go.

141
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Oh, my God.

142
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,000
That's really comfortable.

143
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Oh.

144
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,000
What was it like for Christmas, little boy?

145
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
I don't know. I didn't know you were going to ask me that.

146
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
Well, why did you think it was going to happen?

147
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,000
I didn't know.

148
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Nobody's ever let me sit on their lap before.

149
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,000
All right, just say some toys, please.

150
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Can you give me some choices?

151
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Because I really don't want to mess up on this list.

152
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Kevin, come on.

153
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,000
What about if I tell you the things I don't want?

154
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,000
Okay. Get off. Get off.

155
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Oh, God.

156
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,000
I didn't even get to tell you what I wanted.

157
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Okay, you know what you get?

158
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,000
You get 1,000 helium balloons attached to you,

159
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,000
so Santa doesn't have to go through this again.

160
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Oh, awesome.

161
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,000
Put the sleeve.
